==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Squeezer
<hw>Squeez"er</hw> <pr>(skw⟦emac⟧z"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who, or that which, squeezes; <as>as, a lemon
<ex>squeezer</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Forging)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A machine like a
large pair of pliers, for shingling, or squeezing, the balls of metal
when puddled; -- used only in the plural.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A
machine of several forms for the same purpose; -- used in the
singular.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squeezing</ent>⟦br⟧
